main event: A record card from Project 10073 documents two UFO sightings in Columbus, Ohio.
interesting points: The first sighting was on December 22, 1957, where a blueish-green object moved from NW to SE for a very short period of time., The second sighting was on September 10, 1957, involving an object that moved to SE and was observed for 2-3 minutes., Military sources reported both sightings., The conclusions of the sightings included potential explanations such as meteor, balloon, aircraft, and astronomical phenomena., No photographs were included in either of the reports.
sighted object: one blueish-green object and an unspecified object
